<subSubSection id="F5D16544FF9EAF304C1AFE50FB296F85" pageId="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="BD7436CFFF9EAF304C1AFE50FC536FD9" blockId="6.[827,1444,428,1155]" pageId="6">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304C1AFE50FBA06A9B" box="[827,1119,428,450]" italics="true" pageId="6">Comments on karyotypes:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D95A4B3EFF9EAF304B4AFE50FA5C6A98" author="Shaarawi FAI &amp; Angus RB" box="[1131,1443,428,450]" pageId="6" pagination="105 - 110" refId="ref22330" refString="Shaarawi FAI, Angus RB. 1991 a. Chromosomal analysis of some European species of the genus Berosus Leach (Coleoptera Hydrophilidae). Koleopterologische Rundschau 61: 105 - 110." type="journal article" year="1991">
Shaarawi &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="7F0FF82DFF9EAF304BDDFE50FABA6A9B" box="[1276,1349,428,449]" country="United Kingdom" name="Angus" pageId="6">Angus</collectingRegion>
(1991a)
</bibRefCitation>
published the karyotype data of three species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304C8BFE16FBFC6AA5" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[938,1027,490,511]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304C8BFE16FBFC6AA5" box="[938,1027,490,511]" italics="true" pageId="6">Berosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304B2EFE16FABF6AA5" authority="Brulle, 1835" authorityName="Brulle" authorityYear="1835" box="[1039,1344,489,511]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304B2EFE16FB4B6AA4" box="[1039,1204,489,511]" italics="true" pageId="6">Berosus affinis</emphasis>
Brullé, 1835
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304A6BFE16FB976944" authority="(Linnaeus, 1761)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1761" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luridus">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304A6BFE16FC6C6947" italics="true" pageId="6">Berosus luridus</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1761)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304B89FDF5FBE06967" authority="(Charpentier, 1825)" baseAuthorityName="Charpentier" baseAuthorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signaticollis">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304B89FDF5FA5C6947" box="[1192,1443,520,542]" italics="true" pageId="6">Berosus signaticollis</emphasis>
(Charpentier, 1825)
</taxonomicName>
] and two species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304C1AFDB9FC466900" box="[827,953,581,602]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Enoplurus">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304C1AFDB9FC466900" box="[827,953,581,602]" italics="true" pageId="6">Enoplurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304CEAFDBAFA5D6901" authority="Reiche &amp; Saulcy, 1856" authorityName="Reiche &amp; Saulcy" authorityYear="1856" box="[971,1442,581,603]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispina">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304CEAFDBAFB746900" box="[971,1163,581,603]" italics="true" pageId="6">Berosus bispina</emphasis>
Reiche &amp; Saulcy, 1856
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304C51FD99FB336920" authority="Kuwert, 1888" authorityName="Kuwert" authorityYear="1888" box="[880,1228,612,634]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvus">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304C51FD99FBDF6923" box="[880,1056,612,634]" italics="true" pageId="6">Berosus fulvus</emphasis>
Kuwert, 1888
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="D95A4B3EFF9EAF304A33FD98FC7B69C3" author="Angus RB &amp; Aouad N &amp; Shaarawi FAI" pageId="6" pagination="133 - 139" refId="ref19940" refString="Angus RB, Aouad N, Shaarawi FAI. 1994. The karyotypes of Berosus (s. str.) affinis Brulle and B. (s. str.) hispanicus Kuster, with notes on the egg cocoons (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae). Koleopterologische Rundschau 64: 133 - 139." type="journal article" year="1994">
<collectingRegion id="7F0FF82DFF9EAF304A33FD98FAA26923" box="[1298,1373,612,633]" country="United Kingdom" name="Angus" pageId="6">Angus</collectingRegion>
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304A46FD99FA5C6923" box="[1383,1443,612,634]" italics="true" pageId="6">et al.</emphasis>
(1994)
</bibRefCitation>
added 
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304CFDFD7FFBC769C2" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[988,1080,643,664]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304CFDFD7FFBC769C2" box="[988,1080,643,664]" italics="true" pageId="6">Berosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(s.s.) 
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304B5EFD7FFA6069C2" authority="Kuster, 1847" authorityName="Kuster" authorityYear="1847" box="[1151,1439,643,664]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispanicus">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304B5EFD7FFB0169C2" box="[1151,1278,643,664]" italics="true" pageId="6">hispanicus</emphasis>
Küster, 1847
</taxonomicName>
. The karyotype has 2 
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304B17FD5EFBBA69ED" box="[1078,1093,674,695]" italics="true" pageId="6">n</emphasis>
= 16 + Xy p (
<specimenCount id="ABCDFD46FF9EAF304BF9FD5EFB1469ED" box="[1240,1259,674,695]" pageId="6" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
), in all species except 
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304CABFD3DFB8C698F" baseAuthorityName="Charpentier" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[906,1139,704,726]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signaticollis">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304CABFD3DFB8C698F" box="[906,1139,704,726]" italics="true" pageId="6">Berosus signaticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has an extra pair of autosomes 2 
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304CE6FD23FC2969AE" box="[967,982,735,756]" italics="true" pageId="6">n</emphasis>
= 18 + Xy 
<subScript id="214F348AFF9EAF304B66FD12FBB069A0" attach="left" box="[1095,1103,750,762]" fontSize="5" pageId="6">p</subScript>
(
<specimenCount id="ABCDFD46FF9EAF304B7FFD23FB8E69AE" box="[1118,1137,735,756]" pageId="6" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
). The karyotype of 
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304A6BFD23FC7C6848" authorityName="Brulle" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304A6BFD23FC7C6848" italics="true" pageId="6">Berosus affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may have an additional pair of B-chromosomes. The parachute configuration is shown by meiotic preparations of 
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304CD7FCC7FB18680A" baseAuthorityName="Charpentier" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[1014,1255,827,848]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signaticollis">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304CD7FCC7FB18680A" box="[1014,1255,827,848]" italics="true" pageId="6">Berosus signaticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. C-banding was not attempted; however, the chromosomes appear elongate and with small centromeric constrictions suggesting that the centromeric C-bands are small. 
<bibRefCitation id="D95A4B3EFF9EAF304C1AFC49FBE36891" author="Agarawal U" box="[827,1052,949,971]" pageId="6" pagination="404 - 405" refId="ref19388" refString="Agarawal U. 1960 b. Chromosomes of Berosus indicus. Current Science 10: 404 - 405." type="journal article" year="1960">Agarawal (1960b)</bibRefCitation>
presents data on mitosis and meiosis of 
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304C94FC29FC7D6F52" authority="(Motschulsky, 1861)" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1861" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indicus" subGenus="Enoplurus">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304C94FC29FBF068B0" box="[949,1039,981,1002]" italics="true" pageId="6">Berosus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304B3EFC28FB6768B3" box="[1055,1176,980,1001]" italics="true" pageId="6">Enoplurus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304B89FC28FB0268B3" box="[1192,1277,980,1001]" italics="true" pageId="6">indicus</emphasis>
(Motschulsky, 1861)
</taxonomicName>
, providing the meioformula 8 + Xy 
<subScript id="214F348AFF9EAF304A64FBFEFAB26F54" attach="left" box="[1349,1357,1026,1038]" fontSize="5" pageId="6">p</subScript>
which agrees with newer data; the species identification by 
<bibRefCitation id="D95A4B3EFF9EAF304C1AFBCCFBEE6F1C" author="Agarawal U" box="[827,1041,1072,1094]" pageId="6" pagination="404 - 405" refId="ref19388" refString="Agarawal U. 1960 b. Chromosomes of Berosus indicus. Current Science 10: 404 - 405." type="journal article" year="1960">Agarawal (1960b)</bibRefCitation>
may be easily incorrect since no reliable identification key for Asian 
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304BF5FBB3FAD26F3E" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[1236,1325,1103,1124]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Berosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8FBFEADDFF9EAF304BF5FBB3FAD26F3E" box="[1236,1325,1103,1124]" italics="true" pageId="6">Berosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
existed at that time.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD7436CFFF9EAF304B26FB3BFB296F85" blockId="6.[1031,1238,1223,1248]" box="[1031,1238,1223,1248]" pageId="6">
TRIBE 
<taxonomicName id="7ACB4D4CFF9EAF304B75FB37FB296F85" box="[1108,1238,1227,1247]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Laccobiini">LACCOBIINI</taxonomicName>
